<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="423" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,539,727,752]" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Ecology and natural history.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1802" box="[546,789,727,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="22" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis box="[546,631,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">Calotes</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[675,789,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="423">versicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a diurnal lizard, semi-arboreal to arboreal in habit, and so far, has been recorded mostly in scrub, deciduous forests and plantations. Individuals were mostly seen perching on shrubs, hedges, gardens and along compound walls of houses in villages along forests. 
